post.body: I haven't had a legit reason to post anything since I created this account, but I'm glad I have it.

I'm gonna start sharing links to my own content on this network moving forward. Some of it will be about ZeroNet, so it'll be good to get some feedback from you guys. I've also got a domain reserved in case I'm unable to host it anywhere else.

Offline, things are getting better to an extent. I can't say the same for anything happening online just yet, but this network and other projects have the potential to render "cancelling" a waste of time. They just need a few more smart guys to take them for test drives, check under the hood, and use them to build new sites/platforms.

Integrating WebTorrent With ZeroNet

Not every ZeroNet site needs to use it, but a select few may see some improvement after deploying the client.
